The paper proposes a cooperative decentralized deep learning architecture that utilizes blockchain technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with decentralized processing. The paper also discusses privacy-preserving mechanisms, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
